Description: Fragment of handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Fresh breaks. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine orange-buff.
Curator's comments: Name Timotheos. Probably same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.122, 25. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0677?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1028)
